ple have busted their balls getting to those zones, and dieing repeatedly trying to figure out tactics to beat Behemoth, Aerin Dar, Grummus, and Terris Thule.  Not to mention the sub flags needed to access the bosses themselves.<br>
<br>
But I'm in 2 minds about it.  I've seen the bottlenecks in Valor and BoT, and was glad to get away from them to nicer exp zones.  So, I can understand where the frustration is coming from.  But just opening it up seriously trivialises what people went through to get there.  2 months after the flags are removed, no-one will give a crap that you actually HAVE the flags, outside of guilds working towards the elemental planes.<br>
<br>
I like the quest needed to get to BoT personally, was relatively simple, only took a day or 2, and you could get multiple people flagged at a time basically.  Quests like that should be the way they should open the zones up.  In my opinion of course.  Keep the current flag mobs for mass flaggings, but have a series of short group oriented quests that can achieve the same thing.<br>
<br>
Put the quests on a par with the mobs in the new zone, and if people can do the quests they have an understanding what is ahead of them.  This way people still need to work for the new zones, but they wont be as unavailable to most as they are.<br>
<br>
My biggest fear will be people going into HoH, Tactics, CoD, etc wearing Thurg armor, or the equiv.  Personally, BoT was harder than HoH, or at least on a par with it.  My second biggest fear (more a worry than a fear) will be people heading to these zones being curious.  Be interesting to see how many people spark a Carpin cycle in CoD for example...<br>
<br>
