<br>
PoS/PoV.. some nice exp and &quot;camps&quot; (which are not in SOE's *vision* anyway).<br>
<br>
BoT is another. It can support quite a few &quot;camps&quot;.<br>
<br>
HoH .. a few camps, kill or despawn the Triggers and that ends those Events.<br>
<br>
CoD.. a few camps, then folks kill or despawn Caprin and that blows that Event.<br>
<br>
PoTactics.. don't make me laugh.. can support maybe 3 or 4 *camps*. And when someone goes to do the RZ Event, which kills the folks that won't leave the zone when the Event is taking place, and then they complain.<br>
<br>
Now.. ALL of these are easily accessed by anyone 46 + NOW. You do the PoJ trial, get 'flagged' for PoS/PoV. Do a few quests and get access to all the above.<br>
<br>
These are the only places you can conceivably go to exp. <br>
<br>
ALL zones above that are strictly Raiding Zones. And I do believe SOE said so when they released PoP. And I quote, from the box the expansion came in.. &quot;heighten the level of strategy and push *team* skills to the limit, ultimately separating the weak from the resilient&quot;. And .. &quot;20 new planar zones full of *scripted events* and dynamic content that will challenge the most skilled players&quot;. NO WHERE does it say &quot;come one, come all, new camps and new experience places&quot;. <br>
